[00:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Most people think finance videos need somebody on camera, a creator talking through the market, an entire recording setup, a polished voice over, and you can\'t forget about the charts, the headlines, and hours of editing. But in reality, finance content is mostly built from information, a topic, a script, a'

[00:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'chart, a few headlines, and most importantly a clear point of view. So, what if you could take one finance topic and turn it into an entire faceless channel from scratch? A full long-form finance video, your own personalized AI avatar or voice over, stock charts, and'

[00:27] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'other visuals, short-form clips, of course, and a newsletter or just other text-based social posts. All from just one finance topic. So, of course, this is episode 7 of the AI faceless influencer series. And if you couldn\'t'

[00:39] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'guess already, we\'re going over the finance niche. And before we start, if you end up liking this video and it ends up helping you out, make sure to leave a like and subscribe. It means so much to us, especially how far we\'ve already came. But with that being said, let\'s get started. Finance creators are in a'

[00:52] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'pretty unique spot because they definitely don\'t always need to film a lifestyle video. They definitely don\'t always need to film a vlog. And they don\'t always need the camera pointed directly at their face. A lot of finance content just starts with one main thing,'

[01:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'information. A stock moving, an earnings report, a market headline, a crypto update, a business story, or any financial concept that people would want explained. And once you have the topic itself, the workflow after that is super'

[01:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'simple. Turn the topic into a script, turn the script into a video, add visuals that build trust and reinforce your info, and repurpose the final video into more content. So, for this example, we\'re going to build a fully faceless finance channel from scratch, all using'

[01:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'AI inside of HeyGen. But before we start, we need a topic. This could be any one of the previous topics that we just mentioned or from this list right here. Today, we\'re going to be using a stock market update as our example, specifically Apple\'s stock dropping after their AI announcement. The goal'

[01:42] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'isn\'t just to say whether the stock went up or down. The goal is to explain why people care, what happened, why it even matters, and what viewers should know and watch for next. And that structure is what turns a random headline into a full-blown video. But now, once we have'

[01:54] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'our topic, we need to turn it into an actual script. For finance content, the script needs to be pretty simple, clear, fast, informational, and super easy to understand. Because if the video gets too complicated, or it\'s just a hassle to follow, people will click off. So, I'

[02:07] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'like using an incredibly simple structure. Start with a hook, then what happened, why it matters, and what the viewer should watch for next. And now, for actually writing your script, I would recommend using ChatGPT, Claude, or HeyGen\'s built-in script feature. So,'

[02:19] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'for this example, I could use a prompt like, "Write a short video script about Apple stock dropping after its AI announcements. Start with a strong hook in the first 3 seconds. Explain what happened, why it matters, and what viewers should watch for next. Keep it'

[02:32] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'clear, fast-paced, and easy to understand." Now, the first script that pops out is usually not the one you should use. It\'s a good starting point, but I would still clean it up to make it sound more realistic and human. Because finance scripts are super easy to'

[02:44] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'accidentally make boring, especially if they end up sounding like a corporate report. For example, if the script says something like, "Apple experienced downward pressure due to investor concerns about artificial intelligence." I mean, yeah, like we\'ve already talked about, it\'s true, but it just does not'

[02:57] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'sound like something that people would want to watch. So, I would make it more direct and more personable. And you can ask AI to do that exact thing. And now, this is our new hook: "Apple stock is falling hard and fast, and the reason is AI." It\'s immediately way faster, more'

[03:09] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'natural, and makes the viewer want to keep watching. And you can make as many iterations of the script as you want until you like it. And once you get a result that you like, just copy it or put it off to the side, cuz we\'re going to need it for a later step when we turn this into a full video. But now, before'

[03:21] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'we make the video, we need a host. And we need to decide how it\'s going to be presented. Inside HeyGen, you have a few good options to pick from. You can have an AI avatar of yourself. Think of it as like an on-screen clone. You could also have a default avatar if you don\'t want'

[03:33] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'to be the one on camera. And you can pick from hundreds of different super realistic ones that we have. Or you can make the video fully voice-over led. And for a finance channel, all three of these can work just as well as any of the other ones. One avatar clone can'

[03:45] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'make the content feel a lot more consistent, like it has one host. A default avatar can be a little bit quicker, and it\'s a lot more useful for people who don\'t want to end up on camera. And an AI voice, of course, can feel super good if you just want a voice-over led video. Like if you want'

[03:58] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'it to just feel like a clean market recap. Any of these options will not make or break your channel. The most important thing is consistency. If people are coming back time and time again for market updates, they should feel like the channel has a recognizable'

[04:10] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'style. So, for this example, I\'m going to end up using the avatar hosted one, which is the clone of myself. But, you can use the same exact video workflow with a default avatar or just voice-over to get pretty much the same exact outcome. And with those, you can just'

[04:22] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'let the charts, the headlines, and the visuals do a little more of the heavy lifting. But now, if you do want to go the route of putting yourself in the video and making a clone, let\'s go over how to do that quick. So, inside HeyGen from the main dashboard, go all the way over to the left sidebar and click'

[04:34] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'avatars. Then hit the create avatar button in the top right. HeyGen will ask whether you want a photo or a video avatar. There is a few differences between each of them, but I almost always recommend a video avatar just cuz it usually comes out more realistic. And'

[04:46] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'because if you\'re trying to teach something, trust matters a ton. So, you want your avatar to look as realistic and like you as possible. So, for this example, we\'re to be picking the video avatar. Now, for the background, just think of something that you think fits the best. That might mean sitting at a'

[04:58] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'desk or in a nice studio, maybe even just a bedroom if you want to make it feel more personal and down-to-earth. And now, the actual footage isn\'t complicated, either. Just aim for around 2 minutes of total footage, filmed in either landscape or portrait, and ideally 1080p quality or higher. And'

[05:11] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'just make sure the file size stays under HeyGen\'s limit that shows you on screen. And once the footage is ready, just drag it into the upload box or click browse and select it. From there, you have to choose your avatar\'s name and pick whether you want to make your own voice'

[05:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'or use the one that they already made for you. If I were you, I would just re-record it cuz it usually comes out sounding way better and way more like you. And now, right after you press upload, you\'ll hit the consent step. This is basically just HeyGen asking you to record a super short consent clip.'

[05:36] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'This is just confirming that the person being turned into the avatar is actually giving consent to be turned into one. And that\'s important for whoever is being turned into an avatar because you really should only be creating avatars of people who know exactly how their face and their likeness is going to be'

[05:49] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'used. But now once you\'re past that step, you can press submit and HeyGen will automatically process it for you. And this really only just takes a few minutes. And to make it even easier, HeyGen will actually send you a notification when it\'s done. And when it\'s done, you can open and preview it.'

[06:01] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'And now once we have the actual script and the host style, we can get on to making the actual video. Inside HeyGen, just go right to the main dashboard and you\'ll see the video agent. In my opinion, this is one of HeyGen\'s best features they\'ve ever made. Since we\'re not starting with an already recorded'

[06:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'video and we\'re starting from scratch, we just have to give HeyGen the avatar, the script, the topic, the visual, and the style that we want. And video agent will compile it all for us. So first, all we got to do is paste the script into the main box. And then click right'

[06:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'here and scroll all the way down and we\'re going to give HeyGen some direction. I\'m going to flash up the prompt that I\'m going to be using on screen right now. This is kind of just a guide video agent to make the video exactly how I want it to be. And I\'ll make sure to leave this down in the'

[06:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'description below so you guys can get every single prompt that I\'ve been using. And now once we did that, we can go ahead and select our AI avatar and our AI voice. If you\'re using a cloned avatar like I am, you can select it from right here. Or if you\'re using a default avatar, just press this button right'

[06:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'here. Or if you\'re using a voiceover style, you can just press the little X on the avatar and get rid of it. And then just go over and pick a voice or clone your own. Then we can go ahead and make sure the format looks good. Vertical if you\'re making a short, a reel, or a TikTok. And horizontal if'

[07:02] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'you\'re making a longer YouTube video or maybe even a video for LinkedIn. For this example, I\'m going to keep it vertical cuz finance updates work really well in short form. But now once the script, voice, and format is all ready to go, we can add the visuals that we want HeyGen to use for us. Just gather'

[07:15] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'up a few charts or headlines that you want to be in the video and you can just drag all of those into this box right here. And video agent is going to automatically include them in your video. And now once you have everything together, we can go ahead and click'

[07:27] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'generate. And now in the background, HeyGen\'s turning our idea into an actual video without you even needing to film for it. Apple stock is falling hard and the reason is AI. So here\'s what happened. Apple showed off new Siri and Apple intelligence updates, but'

[07:40] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'investors were not impressed. Instead of seeing a major AI breakthrough, Wall Street saw another step forward, but not enough proof that Apple is leading the AI race. And that matters because Apple needs AI to feel like a reason to upgrade, [music] not just another'

[07:53] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'software feature. And right now, companies like Google, Microsoft, OpenAI, and Meta are making AI feel like the main event. While Apple is still trying to prove that its AI can actually change how people use their devices. So, what should viewers watch for next?'

[08:05] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Watch whether these AI features actually drive iPhone upgrades. Because if they do, this sell-off could just be temporary. But if not, Apple may have a much bigger AI problem than investors expected. And now, once the video is created, you\'re going to want to review'

[08:18] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'it like any other normal creator would. Does the hook hit quickly? Does the video actually explain what happened? Does it explain why it matters? Are the visuals actually supporting the points you\'re making? Is the pacing fast enough? And does it avoid sounding like financial jargon? If something feels'

[08:31] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'off, just tighten the script, swap a visual or two, change the voice or adjust the pacing, or just generate a completely new version of it. This way, you can really make sure it doesn\'t just feel like an AI draft, but an actual video ready to be put on a channel. And'

[08:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'once it feels clear and polished, you now have a fully completed faceless AI video built from a topic and not a lick of recording for it. And now that our main video is done, we can turn the same finance video into a so much more content. We can turn it into a YouTube'

[08:56] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'short, a TikTok, an Instagram reel, a newsletter, a social post. We can use an alternate hook, and we can even make a translated version. And that was a lot to say because there is a lot of options. And this is really where the workflow shows how powerful it'

[09:09] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'can be. Because now you\'re not just making one finance video, you\'re building an entire video system. All created from scratch and without recording a traditional video. You know, the goal isn\'t just to make finance content faster. The goal is to make it'

[09:21] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'efficient and repeatable. Because once you have this workflow set, you could do it over and over again for pretty much anything in the finance niche. So, everybody, if you\'re trying to make a faceless finance channel, this is without a doubt the best workflow you'

[09:34] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'can use for it. And I would highly recommend stealing it. And if you want more AI workflow breakdowns just like this one, make sure to like and subscribe so you don\'t miss out on the next episode of this series, which I\'m sad to say is actually the finale. It\'s been a very fun last seven episodes, but'

